import { Component, OnInit } from '@angular/core'; @Component({ selector: 'n2-others-serb-table', templateUrl: './others-serb-table.component.html', styleUrls: ['./others-serb-table.component.scss'] }) export class OthersSerbTableComponent implements OnInit { constructor() { console.log("test"); } ngOnInit(): void { console.log("test"); } }
SERB Table
Self Employed Professions Net Income Percentage (NIP) Net Income Percentage (for trainings starting 1 May 2020)
Independent Contractors / Sub Contractors / Freelance / Others 80% 80%
General Commission Agents / Sale Agents 80% 75%
Remisiers / Brokers 80% 75%
Insurance / Property Agents 65% 75%
Insurance Managers 65% 80%
Exception: if ratio of total overriding commission / total commission is more than 0.2, a NIP of 0% would be applied to the claim. As insurance managers are not allowed to claim MUP for overriding commissions but they still incur expenses to generate the non-payable overriding commissions, a 50% discount of the expenses is applied. However, NIP will be capped at 80% in the absence of tax documents 75% 80%
Tutors/Music Teachers/Gym Instructors/Coach 90% 90%
